message:
This film depicts the efforts of Om Prakash, a former bonded child laborer and International Children's Peace Prize laureate, who took initiative to educate and give happiness to the poor children in Jaipur and nearby villages. Footprints is a National project that we as AIESEC run in India, volunteers from around the world travel to India to contribute and do their bit towards this. The Goal number 4 from the 17 Sustainable Development Goals UN has for our world talks about "Ensure inclusive and equitable quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all". Read more here:http://www.globalgoals.org/global-goals/quality-education/
Credits: Shabbir Mohammed
